sEmpty [] = true`\n* `isEmpty [a] = false`\n* `isEmpty [a, b] = false`\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.isEmpty\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">isEmpty</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/df668f00e6c08cb63661aacc43d0e83388e2c60d/src/Init/Data/List/Basic.lean#L168-L171","name":"List.eraseIdx","line":168,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.eraseIdx","doc":"`O(i)`. `eraseIdx l i` removes the `i`'th element of the list `l`.\n* `erase [a, b, c, d, e] 0 = [b, c, d, e]`\n* `erase [a, b, c, d, e] 1 = [a, c, d, e]`\n* `erase [a, b, c, d, e] 5 = [a, b, c, d, e]`\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/List/Basic.html#List.eraseIdx\"><span class=\"name\">List</span>.<span class=\"name\">eraseIdx</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{α : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#List\">List</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://